</div> <!--[if lt IE 9]><noscript><div class="page"></noscript><![endif]--> <header class="page"> <h1 class="blogName">CNET Conversations</h1> </header> <!--[if lt IE 9]><noscript></div></noscript><![endif]--> </div> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div id="contentBody" section="mncol"></noscript> <![endif]--> <section id="contentBody" section="mncol">  <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div></noscript> <![endif]--> <article> <div id="postId57556654" class='postBody post list first' section="txt"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="headerTag" section="title"></noscript> <![endif]--> <header section="title"> <h2><a href="/8301-30966_3-57556654-262/how-ford-makes-its-cars-smarter/" commentCount="13">How Ford makes its cars smarter</a></h2> </header> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <a href="/8301-30966_3-57556654-262/how-ford-makes-its-cars-smarter/"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="figureTag"></noscript> <![endif]--> <figure> <span> <img src="http://asset1.cbsistatic.com/cnwk.1d/i/tim/2012/12/02/mascarenas_220x157.jpg" alt="How Ford makes its cars smarter" width="220" height="157" /> </span> </figure> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> </a> <p>I remember when <a href="http://media.ford.com/article_display.cfm?article_id=17257">Paul Mascarenas was named CTO of Ford</a>. It was January 2011, and literally days later he made his way to the CNET stage for a chat at the Consumer Electronics Show. About 18 months later, the company opened its new <a href="http://corporate.ford.com/news-center/press-releases-detail/pr-fords-new-silicon-valley-36681">Silicon Valley Lab</a> to try and emulate the pace of innovation found in the electronics industry. These were very real indications that Mascarenas and Ford would place more than lip service on being in the midst of consumer electronics, and not just in the car business. </p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>Mascarenas is part of CEO Alan Mulally's reinvention of Ford &#8230; <a href="/8301-30966_3-57556654-262/how-ford-makes-its-cars-smarter/" class="readMore">Read more</a></p> <footer> <div class="postByline"> <div id="nameAndTime"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="timeTag datestamp"></noscript> <![endif]--> <time class="datestamp"> December 2, 2012 9:00 PM PST </time> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <span class="author"> By <a rel="author" href="http://www.cnet.com/profile/briancnet/">Brian Cooley</a> </span> </div> </div> <div section="tags" class="tagsWrap"> <div class="postLinks"> <dl> <dt><b>Topics:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?categoryId=1089">Miscellaneous</a> </dd> <dt class="pipe"><b>Tags:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=paul+mascarenas">paul mascarenas</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=brian+cooley">Brian Cooley</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=ford+cto">ford cto</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=ford">ford</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=virttex">virttex</a> </dd> <!-- Added DVAR tag per bug 422649. liaHeader value=paul mascarenas;Brian Cooley;ford cto;ford;virttex --> </dl> </div> <!-- firstCat: 1089 --> </div> </footer> </div><!-- /post --> </article> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div></noscript> <![endif]--> <article> <div id="postId57551482" class='postBody post list' section="txt"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="headerTag" section="title"></noscript> <![endif]--> <header section="title"> <h2><a href="/8301-30966_3-57551482-262/gps-pioneer-takes-aim-at-the-future-of-navigation/" commentCount="6">GPS pioneer takes aim at the future of navigation</a></h2> </header> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <a href="/8301-30966_3-57551482-262/gps-pioneer-takes-aim-at-the-future-of-navigation/"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="figureTag"></noscript> <![endif]--> <figure> <span> <img src="http://asset2.cbsistatic.com/cnwk.1d/i/tim/2012/11/17/rennard_220x157.jpg" alt="GPS pioneer takes aim at the future of navigation" width="220" height="157" /> </span> </figure> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> </a> <p>The pace of modern consumer technology has been so swift in recent decades that you can still meet the people who helped change the world, and find that they're still at it and working on what's next. <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/bob-rennard/11/816/254">Bob Rennard</a> is an example.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>He was one of the developers of the GPS technology we rely on today, and is a co-founder of <a href="http://www.telenav.com/">TeleNav</a>, a provider of GPS-related software and services. The company called me and offered to have Rennard explain its <a href="http://www.telenav.com/products/scout/">Scout</a> platform. I'm normally reticent to come do a story on a product pitch, but the key &#8230; <a href="/8301-30966_3-57551482-262/gps-pioneer-takes-aim-at-the-future-of-navigation/" class="readMore">Read more</a></p> <footer> <div class="postByline"> <div id="nameAndTime"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="timeTag datestamp"></noscript> <![endif]--> <time class="datestamp"> November 18, 2012 9:00 PM PST </time> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <span class="author"> By <a rel="author" href="http://www.cnet.com/profile/briancnet/">Brian Cooley</a> </span> </div> </div> <div section="tags" class="tagsWrap"> <div class="postLinks"> <dl> <dt><b>Topics:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?categoryId=1089">Miscellaneous</a> </dd> <dt class="pipe"><b>Tags:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=connected+gps">connected gps</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=bob+rennard">bob rennard</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=brian+cooley">Brian Cooley</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=gps+apps">gps apps</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=telenav">telenav</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=telenav+scout">telenav scout</a> </dd> <!-- Added DVAR tag per bug 422649. liaHeader value=connected gps;bob rennard;Brian Cooley;gps apps;telenav; --> </dl> </div> </div> </footer> </div><!-- /post --> </article> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <!-- MAC T 2B0.2B1.2B4.2B5 --><!-- MAC [r20120816-1010-dataManipAddDnsBufSize:1.13.14] phx1-rb-tron-xw3.cnet.com::1756559680 2013.02.11.22.11.17 --><!-- MAC-AD STATUS: COULD NOT MAP ( _MAPPINGS='NEWS' BRAND='5' SITE='3' SP='174' CNET-PTYPE='00' POS='100' NCAT='10784:30966:B262:' CNET-PARTNER-ID='1' ) TO _RGROUP --><!-- NO AD TEXT: _QUERY_STRING="PREHTML=%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22infoboardWrap%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22infoboard%22%3E&POSTHTML=%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E&PTYPE=8300&NCAT=10784%3A30966%3AB262%3A&POS=100&SP=174" _REQ_NUM="0"  --><!-- MAC ad --> <!-- MAC T 2B5.2B6.2B9.2BA --><!-- MAC [r20120816-1010-dataManipAddDnsBufSize:1.13.14] phx1-rb-tron-xw3.cnet.com::1756559680 2013.02.11.22.11.17 --><!-- MAC-AD STATUS: COULD NOT MAP ( _MAPPINGS='NEWS' BRAND='5' SITE='3' SP='104' CNET-PTYPE='00' POS='100' NCAT='10784:30966:B262:' CNET-PARTNER-ID='1' ) TO _RGROUP --><!-- NO AD TEXT: _QUERY_STRING="PREHTML=%3Cdiv%20id%3D%22exclusiveResource%22%3E&POSTHTML=%3C%2Fdiv%3E&PTYPE=8300&NCAT=10784%3A30966%3AB262%3A&POS=100&SP=104" _REQ_NUM="0"  --><!-- MAC ad --> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div></noscript> <![endif]--> <article> <div id="postId57544841" class='postBody post list' section="txt"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="headerTag" section="title"></noscript> <![endif]--> <header section="title"> <h2><a href="/8301-30966_3-57544841-262/whats-next-from-the-people-who-invented-the-pc/" commentCount="42">What's next from the people who invented the PC?</a></h2> </header> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <a href="/8301-30966_3-57544841-262/whats-next-from-the-people-who-invented-the-pc/"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="figureTag"></noscript> <![endif]--> <figure> <span> <img src="http://asset0.cbsistatic.com/cnwk.1d/i/tim/2012/11/04/parc_image_220x157.jpg" alt="What's next from the people who invented the PC?" width="220" height="157" /> </span> </figure> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> </a> <p> Xerox's <a href="http://www.parc.com/">Palo Alto Research Center</a> is a legendary and often misunderstood place. Once Xerox's outpost in Silicon Valley, it's now a separate company within Xerox, and it focuses on applied R&amp;D. PARC is where you'll find <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PARC_%28company%29">the beginnings of the personal computer, LAN, voice command, and laser printing</a>. Today its work branches far beyond computing, with a strong emphasis on ethnography, the study of what people do and how they do it.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>I'd met <a href="http://www.xerox.com/innovation/xerox-innovation-group/sophie-vandebroek/enus.html">Xerox CTO Sophie Vandebroek</a> before, but was curious to see how things were going on this 10th anniversary of &#8230; <a href="/8301-30966_3-57544841-262/whats-next-from-the-people-who-invented-the-pc/" class="readMore">Read more</a></p> <footer> <div class="postByline"> <div id="nameAndTime"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="timeTag datestamp"></noscript> <![endif]--> <time class="datestamp"> November 4, 2012 9:00 PM PST </time> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <span class="author"> By <a rel="author" href="http://www.cnet.com/profile/briancnet/">Brian Cooley</a> </span> </div> </div> <div section="tags" class="tagsWrap"> <div class="postLinks"> <dl> <dt><b>Topics:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?categoryId=1089">Miscellaneous</a> </dd> <dt class="pipe"><b>Tags:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=sophie+vandebroek">sophie vandebroek</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=brian+cooley">Brian Cooley</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=digital+nursing">digital nursing</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=xerox+parc">xerox parc</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=digital+parking+meters">digital parking meters</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=parc">parc</a> </dd> <!-- Added DVAR tag per bug 422649. liaHeader value=sophie vandebroek;Brian Cooley;digital nursing;xerox parc;digital parking meters; --> </dl> </div> </div> </footer> </div><!-- /post --> </article> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div></noscript> <![endif]--> <article> <div id="postId57533990" class='postBody post list' section="txt"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="headerTag" section="title"></noscript> <![endif]--> <header section="title"> <h2><a href="/8301-30966_3-57533990-262/the-lights-over-your-head-are-about-to-get-smart/" commentCount="14">The lights over your head are about to get smart</a></h2> </header> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <a href="/8301-30966_3-57533990-262/the-lights-over-your-head-are-about-to-get-smart/"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="figureTag"></noscript> <![endif]--> <figure> <span> <img src="http://asset0.cbsistatic.com/cnwk.1d/i/tim/2012/10/17/Bridgelux-Array-Product-Family-1_220x157.jpg" alt="The lights over your head are about to get smart" width="220" height="157" /> </span> </figure> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> </a> <p> Take a walk through the labs of <a href="http://bridgelux.com/assets/files/BL_Fact_Sheet_01-09.pdf">Bridgelux</a> (PDF) in Livermore, Calif., and you see a lot of LED lighting modules being made on a more affordable platform: disused factories that used to make silicon chips. But while you'll see lots of lights, you'll hear mostly about connectivity. Bridgelux <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Watkins_%28Seagate%29">CEO Bill Watkins</a> envisions a new array of smart, connected sensors, cameras, and other devices integrated with LED lighting over our heads.</p> <p></p> <p></p> <p>The challenge is formidable: Most lighting consumers, large and small, think of lighting as a cost to be contained, not an opportunity to be maximized. So job &#8230; <a href="/8301-30966_3-57533990-262/the-lights-over-your-head-are-about-to-get-smart/" class="readMore">Read more</a></p> <footer> <div class="postByline"> <div id="nameAndTime"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="timeTag datestamp"></noscript> <![endif]--> <time class="datestamp"> October 19, 2012 4:50 PM PDT </time> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <span class="author"> By <a rel="author" href="http://www.cnet.com/profile/briancnet/">Brian Cooley</a> </span> </div> </div> <div section="tags" class="tagsWrap"> <div class="postLinks"> <dl> <dt><b>Topics:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?categoryId=1089">Miscellaneous</a> </dd> <dt class="pipe"><b>Tags:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=smart+grid">smart grid</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=brian+cooley">Brian Cooley</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=bridgelux">Bridgelux</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=bill+watkins">Bill Watkins</a>, </dd> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?keyword=led+lighting">LED lighting</a> </dd> <!-- Added DVAR tag per bug 422649. liaHeader value=smart grid;Brian Cooley;Bridgelux;Bill Watkins;LED lighting --> </dl> </div> </div> </footer> </div><!-- /post --> </article> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div></noscript> <![endif]--> <article> <div id="postId57524628" class='postBody post list' section="txt"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="headerTag" section="title"></noscript> <![endif]--> <header section="title"> <h2><a href="/8301-30966_3-57524628-262/mission-impossible-making-the-green-car-cool/" commentCount="34">Mission impossible: Making the green car cool</a></h2> </header> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <a href="/8301-30966_3-57524628-262/mission-impossible-making-the-green-car-cool/"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="figureTag"></noscript> <![endif]--> <figure> <span> <img src="http://asset2.cbsistatic.com/cnwk.1d/i/tim/2012/10/02/henrik_220x157.jpg" alt="Mission impossible: Making the green car cool" width="220" height="157" /> </span> </figure> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> </a> <p> Join us for a real inside tour of the <a href="http://onward.fiskerautomotive.com/en-us">Fisker Automotive</a> design center. Our tour guide is none other then <a href="http://onward.fiskerautomotive.com/en-us/about/fiskerautomotive/">Henrik Fisker</a>. We'll see the Karma through his eyes, view the future of personal transportation, and see the cocktail napkin that started it all. In the end, you may be surprised at how much this is a story of America. </p> <p> </p> <p></p> <p> Henrik Fisker is best known for designing the Aston Martin DB9 and the BMW Z8, both masterpieces in modern auto penmanship. He also did the initial design work on the <a href="http://cnettv.cnet.com/8301-34133_53-57523208-314/can-the-tesla-model-s-unkill-the-electric-car-cnet-on-cars-episode-3/">Tesla Model S</a>, which led to a less than &#8230; <a href="/8301-30966_3-57524628-262/mission-impossible-making-the-green-car-cool/" class="readMore">Read more</a></p> <footer> <div class="postByline"> <div id="nameAndTime"> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript><div class="timeTag datestamp"></noscript> <![endif]--> <time class="datestamp"> October 2, 2012 9:00 PM PDT </time> <!--[if lt IE 9]> <noscript></div></noscript> <![endif]--> <span class="author"> By <a rel="author" href="http://www.cnet.com/profile/briancnet/">Brian Cooley</a> </span> </div> </div> <div section="tags" class="tagsWrap"> <div class="postLinks"> <dl> <dt><b>Topics:</b></dt> <dd> <a href="/8300-5_3-0.html?categoryId=1089">Miscellaneous</a> </dd> <dt class="pipe"><b>Tags:</b></dt> <dd> <a h